      <hedline>
        <hl1>Batter Up! The Battle of New York Is at Hand</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Kenneth R Garcia letter comments on October 19 article on upcoming World Series between New York Yankees and New York Mets</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''It's Root, Root, Root, but for Which Team?'' (front page, Oct. 19):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''It's Root, Root, Root, but for Which Team?'' (front page, Oct. 19):</p>
        <p>Choosing between the Yankees and Mets is difficult. As a kid (now 38) playing Little League baseball in Spring Valley, N.Y., I thought the Yankees were a rather abysmal team.</p>
        <p>The Mets were the only New York team that showed us how to win the big one or get close. Cleon Jones, Tommy Agee, Tom Seaver, Tug McGraw, Nolan Ryan, Ron Swoboda and Ed Kranepool: the Mets always showed courage and luck. Yet the 1990's have brought us the steady, strong Yankees and, again, our determined Mets. Wow!</p>
        <p>I will be rooting for both home teams in this series.</p>
        <p>KENNETH R. GARCIA  Gansevoort, N.Y., Oct. 19, 2000</p>
      </block>
